HB 187 Original 2026 Regular Session Muscarello
Abstract: Repeals provisions regarding a court reporter pool employed by the supreme
court.
Present law establishes a court reporter pool of 30 court reporters employed by the supreme
court for assignment to the various district courts.
Present law provides that court reporters in the pool are in addition to all other court
reporters provided for in the district courts. Further provides that the pool court reporters
have the same qualifications, duties, responsibilities, and pay as reporters in a district court.
Present law requires the supreme court to assign the pool court reporters on a geographical
basis.
Present law provides for an annual salary to pool court reporters of $15,000 paid by the
supreme court from its annual budget. Further limits the travel expenses of pool court
reporters to the amount allowed for other state employees.
Present law allows the judicial administrator to secure court reporting services from a
shorthand court reporting company as needed rather than employing the full quota of pool
court reporters.
